<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870501-0145 </DOCNO><HL> General DynamicsReceives ContractsFor $316.4 Million</HL><DD> 05/01/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GD BA LTV FMC GM ROK HONAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Units of General Dynamics Corp. received contracts totaling $316.4 million for F-16 aircraft improvements for the Air Force and Stinger missile-engineering services and M-1 tank equipment and support for the Army.    Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., won Air Force contracts totaling $236 million for production of Maverick missiles and equipment for bombs.    Boeing Co. units received Air Force contracts totaling $219.1 million for development of the short-range attack missile for bomber aircraft, and for B-52 aircraft-engineering services.    AM General, a unit of LTV Corp., received a $39.7 million Army contract for high-mobility wheeled vehicles.    FMC Corp. won a $35.1 million Army contract for Bradley Fighting Vehicle support.    Rockwell International Corp. units were issued contracts totaling $23.4 million for B-1B aircraft support equipment for the Air Force and navigation equipment for the Air Force and Navy.    Gibbs andamp; Cox got a $19.7 million Navy contract for ship-design services.    Honeywell Inc. won a $17.9 million contract for MX ICBM equipment.    AUL Instruments Inc. received a $13.9 million Air Force contract for Maverick missile-launch equipment. </TEXT></DOC>